THE national shutdown, as ordered by President Cyril Ramaphosa, is in full swing. This in a bid to curtail the spread of the coronavirus. But this important measure has thwarted the plans of Egoliwood’s brightest stars. The latest lockdown victim is former Isibaya actress, Zinhle Mabena, who was forced to ice her scheduled Nyaope Must Fall event. She hosts the annual doo with herhubby, Robert Mabena. Said robert: “We had planned a march against nyaope here in Gauteng, which was a build-up to the main event in North West on 16 June.” He said the event had been shelveduntil further notice. “The event is about putting people’s safety first. We want every province to know about the harmful effects ofnyaope.”